Good. This is a different issue, and it is much simpler.

You are now calling:

```text
GET http://keycloak.ns-keycloak.svc.cluster.local/realms/arthur-local/protocol/openid-connect/token/.well-known/openid-configuration
```

and Keycloak returns:

```text
405 Method Not Allowed
```

That URL is wrong.

The `/.well-known/openid-configuration` path belongs under the **realm**, not under the **token endpoint**.

What you have now is effectively:

```text
.../protocol/openid-connect/token/.well-known/openid-configuration
```

but it should be:

```text
http://keycloak.ns-keycloak.svc.cluster.local/realms/arthur-local/.well-known/openid-configuration
```

Then from that metadata response, you read:

* `authorization_endpoint`
* `token_endpoint`
* `jwks_uri`
* `issuer`

The fix is in how you build or pass `issuerUri`.

Right now your log shows:

```text
Issuer URI : http://keycloak.ns-keycloak.svc.cluster.local/realms/arthur-local/protocol/openid-connect/token
```

That is not an issuer URI. That is the token endpoint.

It should be:

```text
http://keycloak.ns-keycloak.svc.cluster.local/realms/arthur-local
```

So update the value coming from Lancelot or your temporary config.

Use:

```yaml
issuer-uri: http://keycloak.ns-keycloak.svc.cluster.local/realms/arthur-local
```

not:

```yaml
issuer-uri: http://keycloak.ns-keycloak.svc.cluster.local/realms/arthur-local/protocol/openid-connect/token
```

Your discovery flow should look like this:

```java
String issuerUri = appConfig.getIssuerUri(); 
// http://keycloak.ns-keycloak.svc.cluster.local/realms/arthur-local

OidcMetadata metadata = oidcDiscoveryClient.loadMetadata(issuerUri);

// metadata.getAuthorizationEndpoint()
// metadata.getTokenEndpoint()
```

And your discovery client should call:

```java
String discoveryUrl = issuerUri + "/.well-known/openid-configuration";
```

which becomes:

```java
http://keycloak.ns-keycloak.svc.cluster.local/realms/arthur-local/.well-known/openid-configuration
```

Then for token exchange, use the `token_endpoint` returned by discovery, which will be:

```text
http://keycloak.ns-keycloak.svc.cluster.local/realms/arthur-local/protocol/openid-connect/token
```

So the correct sequence is:

1. `issuerUri`

   ```text
   http://keycloak.ns-keycloak.svc.cluster.local/realms/arthur-local
   ```

2. discovery URL

   ```text
   http://keycloak.ns-keycloak.svc.cluster.local/realms/arthur-local/.well-known/openid-configuration
   ```

3. token endpoint from metadata

   ```text
   http://keycloak.ns-keycloak.svc.cluster.local/realms/arthur-local/protocol/openid-connect/token
   ```

Add a quick guard so this does not happen again:

```java
if (issuerUri.contains("/protocol/openid-connect/token")) {
    throw new IllegalArgumentException("issuerUri must be realm base URL, not token endpoint");
}
```

And log both separately:

```java
log.info("Issuer URI={}", issuerUri);
log.info("Discovery URL={}", issuerUri + "/.well-known/openid-configuration");
```

So the immediate fix is: change `appConfig.getIssuerUri()` to the realm base URL only.

After that, this error should disappear, and the next step will likely be the real token exchange.
